TY  - JOUR
TI  - Games Played through Agents
AU  - Prat, Andrea
AU  - Rustichini, Aldo
AB  - [We introduce a game of complete information with multiple principals and multiple common agents. Each agent makes a decision that can affect the payoffs of all principals. Each principal offers monetary transfers to each agent conditional on the action taken by the agent. We characterize pure-strategy equilibria and we provide conditions--in terms of game balancedness--for the existence of an equilibrium with an efficient outcome. Games played through agents display a type of strategic inefficiency that is absent when either there is a unique principal or there is a unique agent.]
